snippet.textDisplay: This one hurt because I had seen a dog for months run away from home, he had different colored eyes, he would run with his little friends, sharing food, water and waiting for one another, it was so cute seeing them, then two weeks prior being told I will never see him again, those last fourteen days I walked him, feed him, went to his house, which was a block away, he would waggle his tail, bathe in the mud his owners let him be present to, he was more than a dog, he had gained my love, I would touch him in the gates, follow him, the last time I carried him was when I went to school, I had never wanted a hug like that before ! I had made a promise to touch him or say hi going to or coming back from school, but I had lacked management, I regret it forever. He had encountered us several times at night when walking my Rottweiler, and this dog ' lobo ' was so friendly, but Rottweilers are too territorial and aggressive I cared more for lobo than my rotti, well being hurt that is. My family knew him for months, and loved him. All until that day. We had passed the house coming from Walmart and I said, " oh hey look ! Mom you think lobo is there ? " she had drenched eyes all the way to our house. I had then asked, but because I thought she cried for a different reason, seeing she does that a lot. we parked, had a moment of silence until she said those words he had died. I did shed three drops to the floor to match the terrible weather that day. I had gone in my house, searched for my Rottweiler then kissed and hugged him. Until then my mom had cared and feed birds that return to our shed, I had loved and been affectionate to ' raskal ' the Rottweiler, bought him food, gave him my sweaters, slept with him, play with him, care for him way more than before. I just wish I didn't lose a dog to start being too protective about another one, since that day I have and will never shop at the ice cream store, where I first met him, my sister had introduced me to lobo and that was the best time I had agreed to see something. His green and blue eyes, his muddy, but yet comforting fur, his little friend and most importantly his encounters at the worst moments, but his perspective he just wanted food and attention or anything he desired I did the best to my ability to make sure he was satisfied. I miss him and seeing how these people saw one on the streets I wonder if that's how Lobos life had finished. Sorry but I just need this to be somewhere, I can finally open due to the topic, sorry it's not the best structure or worded perfectly I just had to put it here..😞💔
